cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper discusses Information Extraction (IE) technology, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions Information Retrieval (IR) technology, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses various sub-tasks of IE, such as Named Entity Recognition and Relation Extraction, which are also relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions Digital Assistants like Siri, Cortana, and Google Now, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
